      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t understand what you mean. \nBy generating types.go from ctypes.go (via \u0027go tool cgo -godefs\u0027) we get a definition of a Go struct where the memory layout matches the corresponding C struct.  This is just a convenience function todo the casting. \nMaybe there is a better way to define it, but I don\u0027t think there is a substantially better way to accomplish this.\nPlease clarify if I misunderstand.",
